CAPE TOWN - A 26-year-old man was arrested in connection with the murder of his 18-month-old stepson, Western Cape police said on Monday.Police spokesperson Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana said officers were informed by workers at a health facility near Kensington of a toddler who died after being brought in with serious injuries to the head and body. The child s 26-year-old stepfather was arrested and his 30-year-old mother taken in for questioning, said Rwexana.The suspect was due to appear in the Cape Town magistrate s court once charged.African News Agency